  "description": [
    "FIVE Medieval Tactics Duplicated in 2Day Attack on Chinese Capital STORM WALLS OF YUNNANFU CITIZENS ARM 300 Killed During Attempt to Rout Usurpers CHlCAGOSanguinary fighting reminiscent of the medieval days has occurred at Yunuanfu cajital of Yunnan province in an effort to dislodge the Kuomintang according to a Peking story copyrighted by The Chicago Tribune Tang Chi yu brother of the famous governor who tied following his brothers death marched on the capital to oust Lung Yin the usurper Heavy fighting took place last week 12 miles distant Lung Yin retired upon the capital when the city of Chengkung fell after heavy fighting Summon Citizens to Walls Tang attacked the capital at ddwn four days later hoping to take it by assault Lacking a suf ficient force the governor sum moned the citizens to she ancient walls where besides rifles molden lead bowlders and other instru ments of death were dropped on the warriors who were attempting to scale the 50 foot walls The battle continued two days and nights with heavy civilian as well as military casualties When Tang withdrew for reorganization 300 dead lay at the foot of the walls and the surrounding country was littered with dead"
